music making as making more than sound this book is an adapted version of the author 's doctoral dissertation . through ethnomusicological study of a music conservatory , prof. kingsbury brought to western music scholars and lovers a widened concepts of music , music talent , and music performance . music is much more than sound structure . music is also & quot ; constructed & quot ; by its social context . comparing the book with the dissertation , the sequence of the chapters is a bit different . there are also some additions in the temple university press book version . it is a thought provoking book for ethnomusicologists , musicologists , anthropologists , and particularly western music lovers